# Server (BE) Conventions

See `AGENTS.md` for full spec. **No JSON Server** — Express + SQLite only.

## Stack

Express + TypeScript + SQLite (better-sqlite3 or similar).

## API contract

Implement exact routes from `AGENTS.md`. Response shapes must match `server/src/types/`.

## Data

- Catalog in SQLite, seeded from `server/data/bundle.json`
- Configurations + configuration_items for shopper state
- Orders table for checkout drafts

## Pricing

- `calculateQuote(catalog, configuration)` in `server/src/lib/pricing/`
- Mirror logic from `client/src/lib/pricing.ts` (or share via path alias)
- Resolve prices from DB only — ignore client-sent prices

## Routes

- `GET /config` — assemble nested BundleConfig from DB
- `PATCH /configurations/:id` — validate body with Zod
- `POST .../quote` — compute Quote
- `POST .../checkout` — quote first, then persist order draft

## Dev

- Port 3001; client proxies `/api` via Vite
- Same port/URLs so FE needs zero changes when switching from local.ts

## Documentation

- Prefer TypeScript types and tests over comments.
- JSDoc only on non-obvious **public** exports (e.g. `calculateQuote`, route handlers with validation edge cases, pricing rules).
- Skip JSDoc on obvious CRUD, mappers, and Zod schemas where types are self-explanatory.
- Mirror client pricing behavior; comment only where server authority differs from client preview.
